SOME PROBLEMS AND POSSIBLE SOLUTIONS
.
1. Do not start the installation, the installer gives an error
.
There are many reasons for this. Two possible reasons are : 
a. The conflict with previous products Adobe. 
Solution: 
Remove the application at a time until the problem is solved. 
b. Applications are removed, a window pops up again. 
Solution: 
We clean the folder% SystemDrive%  Program Files  Common Files  Adobe  Installers  uninstall 
(For x64% SystemDrive%  Program Files (x86)  Common Files  Adobe  Installers  uninstall) 
Adobe. Be careful, the action can lead to problems with other products of Adobe. 
.
2. After patching it is not activated Extended version (in the "About" no mention of Extended)
.
1. Remove the patched file (s) amtlib.dll, by default they are located here: 
For 32: SystemDrive  Program Files  Adobe  Adobe Photoshop CS6 
For 64: SystemDrive  Program Files  Adobe  Adobe Photoshop CS6 (64 Bit) 
....OR.....SystemDrive  Program Files (x86)  Adobe  Adobe Photoshop CS6 
2. Rename the original (amtlib.dll.BAK) to amtlib.dll. 
3. Launch Photoshop, accept the agreement, close. 
4. Use the patch again. 
.
3. No 3D option
.
a. If you have Windows XP, then the item will not be updated engine does not work with 3D in XP (and there may be problems with the new blur filters). Adobe.com: 3D features and some GPU-enabled features are not supported on Windows XP. 
b. If the system is higher than Windows XP, then look at the item 2. "When the patch is not activated Extended Version" 
.
4. In the patcher i can not see the buttons
.
Set the font size in the system to 100% (Control Panel -> Display or RMB on the desktop -> Screen Resolution -> Make text and other elements default). 
.
5. Error when running the tool "plastic", as well as new filters blur ("Blurring the diaphragm," "Blur field"), etc.
.
1. 3D features and some GPU-enabled features are not supported on Windows XP. 
2. If the system is higher than XP, update  install the graphics driver. 
.

.

6. Patcher does not patch files, gives an ERROR message.
 .
 1. You may be in wrong folder.
 2. You may not have admin rights on your system.
 .
 7. The "Update" button is not active
 .
 The button is not active after patching, but the update continues to be checked (if not blocked by firewall).
 Updates can be checked without starting Photoshop.
 For x32:
 Run SystemDrive  Program Files  Common Files  Adobe  OOBE  PDApp  core  PDapp.exe
 For x64:
 Run SystemDrive  Program Files (x86)  Common Files  Adobe  OOBE  PDApp  core  PDapp.exe
 .
 This action is equal to pressing the "Update" button in Photoshop.
 P.S. Create a shortcut for PDapp.exe, if necessary.
 .
 8. Where is the patch, i do not see it.
 .
 1. You may be in wrong folder.
 2. Your security software may delete or quarantine the patch without your knowledge.
 .
 9. I have language problem, how can i change it.
 .
 1. You should select your language at the beginning of installation.
 2. You can not change it after installation.

WIN32/Heur VIRUS
Win32/Heur, or Win32 Heur, is a virus that infects computers through corrupt media files, spam emails and illegitimate file sharing applications. The Win32/Heur virus often creates a fake anti-virus program that pops up on your computer and notifies you that your computer is infected. The Win32/Heur virus also can download additional viruses, slow your computer, redirect your Internet browser, and even cause your computer to crash.
